<br>
There's not even a hint on the delays of weapons used there (everyone knows that faster weapons mean lower dmg per hit, even though they'll have the same DPS), and the LA and DW skills work differently.<br>
<br>
LA will score a lot more hits with the off-hand than DW, which in itself will lower the average dmg per hit, and LA will lower the dmg per hit too to account for the extra number of hits.<br>
<br>
What I mean is that it makes sense that LA average dmg per hit is lower, that's just how skills work. On the other hand LA lands more hits and swing both weapons all the time.<br>
<br>
If you use a SB wielding a 2h and compare average dmg / hit with those of an Inf or a NS, there's no doubt the SB will have a higher dmg / hit. Different skills, different weap delays. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ukedilash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kedilash</A> at: 6/13/02 7:55:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ubilesilhouette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bile Silhouette</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/02 8:18:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> See, <br>
<br>
This is the reason why mill is so frustrated, me as well.<br>
Your post is... well... wrong.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, leftaxe will swing everytime, but to balance that, the swings are as significantly reduced damage.  So much so that DW/CD will outdamage it, pretty significantly.<br>
<br>
The newest change MAY bring max spec or very close to max spec leftaxe into balance with DW/CD, but to break even, an SB must invest massive spec points to bring it to even with dual wield.  Consider that Dual Wield is effective at 1, 20, 40, 50 spec... that is, it is very level based and is effective even when you don't spec in it very much, that tends to have nightshades and infiltrators very high spec'd in weapon, envenom, CS.... WITHOUT losing effectiveness.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lastly, your last point.<br>
<br>
2handed weapons will NOT outdamage Dual Wield/Celtic Dual.<br>
<br>
You'll notice in the patch notes from the latest leftaxe enhancement, leftaxe was enhanced so that it does more damage then 2handers at high spec.<br>
<br>
This is the nature of dual wielding classes vs 2handed classes.  Classes that wield 2 weapons are designed to do more damage... and they do, over time.  Frontloading damage helps for 2hander classes, but, for the most part, the duel wielding classes are going to do MORE damage then 2handed classes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, speed of weapon must be looked at.... but... take the EXACT same weapon for a LEFTAXER and a DW/CD'er and the dw/cd'er will do, on average, a good bit more.<br>
<br>
The equations for Leftaxe and DW/CD are published.  Try using them in calculations and you will see the disparity.<br>
<br>
*** NOTE that the leftaxe equation has changed some in the latest leftaxe enhancement, but only for higher spec (greater then 35, i believe)<br>
<br>
Either way, <br>
<br>
This is the point of everything!<br>
<br>
<br>
DW/CD IS better then Leftaxe in damage.  Period.<br>
<br>
2.5 spec IS better then 50 hitpoints.  Period.  (nightshade spell is better as well)<br>
<br>
Vanish IS better then Shadowrun. (nightshade venom is better as well)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The point of all this..........<br>
<br>
<br>
Balance is out of whack.  Add variance fix for nightshades and we are getting to the point of.... INFILTRATOR &gt; NIGHTSHADE &gt; SHADOWBLADE.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hopefully mill and vehemence can do some testing to prove it.... and mythic will take action to re-balance rogues.<br>
