<br>
I have to raise objection regarding both your and Mill's approach to testing.  What we are after is balance.  Throwing finess, grace, and skill into the equation is a just an excellent way to @#%$ things up.  An individual's level of skill should not be a determining factor on the issue of class balance!  That is just plain silly.  The classes should be balanced according to the sum of their maximum potentials.  If you know anything about statistic you understand that throwing all possible variables into the class soup, so to speak, and calling the result an accurate examination of all constituent factors, such as occurs in a everyday RvR, shows nothing, as you yourself has proved.<br>
<br>
If we really want to address the issue, the *only* reliable testing environment is one where each variable is examined independently and free from influence.  This really is common sense.  Such logs will show us the way things are, but will say nothing towards the way things should be...the old ought vs. is fallacy once again has revealed its ugly head and clouded the issue.<br>
<br>
Until there is consensus on what Shadowblades *ought* to be able to do, revealing what it *is* that they actually do accomplishes nothing other than forcing public awareness to reflect reality, a commendable pursuit, but doesn't do a god dman thing for me.  Encouraging people to log realistic fights is just encouraging them to waste their time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/utiwgy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiwgy </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/02 3:17:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> my CS thrust poisoning Infil is copied over to test server now . i will gladly help in putting this stuff to rest once and for all.  Tell me and where i will be there too  to help post . <br>
